      "text": "al fast-tracking option. ## How to explain D and E In NV ODMR, D is the zero-field splitting, close to 2870 MHz at room temperature. It is mainly set by the internal spin-spin interaction of the NV center and shifts with temperature. E is a transverse strain or electric-field-related splitting parameter. In simple public language, D is the center reference of the spectrum and E describes a small built-in asymmetry of the diamond environment. If D and E are fixed by calibration, the remaining frequency shifts can be interpreted mainly as magnetic-field information. ## Demo talking points for visitors The quantum compass demo can be explained in four sentences. A green laser prepares and reads",
